Create a report showing how many views each keyword has. 
Output the keyword and the total views, and order records with highest view count first.
keywords are [spaghetti,food] in this format in post_keywords column of df

df['postkeywords'] = df['post_keywords'].str.split(',')
df_exploded = df.explode('postkeywords')

df_exploded['postkeywords'] = df_exploded['postkeywords'].str.replace('[', '')
df_exploded['postkeywords'] = df_exploded['postkeywords'].str.replace(']', '')
df_exploded.groupby('postkeywords')['viewer_id'].count().reset_index(name = 'total_views').sort_values(by = 'total_views', ascending = False)

learning -  .explode, to create multiple rows each having one keyword, one row for spaghetti and one for food

