We want to identify the most suspicious claims in each state.]
We'll consider the top 5% of claims (those at or above the 95th percentile of fraud scores) 
in each state as potentially fraudulent.

fraud_score.head()
#fraud_score['totalfraudscore'] = fraud_score.groupby('state')['fraud_score'].transform('sum')
def perc(x):
    return np.percentile(x, 95)
values = fraud_score.groupby('state')['fraud_score'].agg(perc).reset_index(name = 'percentilescore')
df = values.merge(fraud_score, on = 'state', how = 'inner')
df[df['fraud_score'] >= df['percentilescore']]

learning - percentile syntax

